  "metadata": {
    "title": "Probabilistic Identity Resolution: Cross-Device Attribution via Bayesian Graph Networks",
    "doi": "10.5281/zenodo.18860338",
    "publication_date": "2026-03-04",
    "description": "Traditional attribution collapses at the identity layer \u2014 the same customer appears as dozens of anonymous profiles across devices, browsers, and sessions. This paper presents a probabilistic identity resolution framework using Bayesian graph networks with cross-device matching, deterministic anchoring, and privacy-preserving hashing. The framework achieves sub-second resolution at scale with explicit uncertainty quantification, enabling accurate multi-touch attribution across fragmented customer journeys. Complementary to Robinson (2026a) hybrid attribution and Robinson (2026b) media mix modeling.",
